@KM I think you have hit against an element of entering the rebus that some find confusing but which is ultimately meant to make solving the rebus easier: You can always just enter the first letter of a rebus. 

Some people don’t like that because if they leave rebus squares as the last squares they solve, they’ll inevitably be left with a completed puzzle that doesn’t show the full solution. 

In your case it’s hard to say exactly how it all happened, but check puzzle will have validated any squares where you had entered only the first letter, because the rebus always lets you do that. And yes, once it’s checked, you can’t change a square.

